Fred Hassan - Wikipedia




















 






Fred Hassan

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

Fred Hassan (born November 12, 1945, in Multan, Pakistan[1]) is a managing director at Warburg Pincus, which he joined in 2011.[2] He was the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of pharmaceutical company Schering-Plough from 2003 until November 3, 2009, when the company completed its merger with Merck & Co.[3] Hassan was the Chairman of the Board of Bausch & Lomb from March 2010 until its sale in 2013.[4][5] On October 29, 2009 Time Warner announced that Hassan would join their Board of Directors.[6]



